LDP._0026_03_Bibliotecario_RISPOSTA_["eng"] = u"!!!RISPOSTA!!!"
LDP._0026_04_Bibliotecario_SEG_I_CAL_ESA___STR___M_E_QUE_RIS_COR_A_UN_EVE_NON_ANC_AVV_["eng"] = u"Following the calculations, precisely %s m. And this result corresponds to an event that has not yet occurred..."
LDP._0026_05_Bibliotecario_MMH_NO_DEV_AVE_SBA_DEI_CAL_RIP_CON_UNA_VEL_DI___STR___MS_LA_RIS_GIU_ERA___STR___M_TI_FAC_VED_["eng"] = u"<*>#italic#Mmh...<*> no, you must have miscalculated. Try again with a speed of %s m/s. The right answer was %s m, I'll show you."
LDP._0027_01_Bibliotecario_QUE_CHE_ABB_APP_FAT_DIM_UNA_COS_MOL_IMP_LA_MAT_CHE_COM_LA_REA_SEG_DEL_REG_BEN_PRE_ORA_SE_CON_MA_INT_TUT_CI_CHE__PER_ESI_UNA_RAG_PER_CUI_GLI_ESS_VIV_ESS_ANC_PER_E_FAT_DI_MAT_NON_DOV_SEG_LE_STE_REG_["eng"] = u"What we've just done demonstrates one very important thing: the matter that makes up reality follows very specific rules. Now, if by \"matter\" we mean everything that is perceptible, is there a reason why living beings - being perceptible and made of matter - should not follow the same rules?"
LDP._0027_02_Tu_BEH_UN_ESS_VIV_HA_QUA_IN_PI_RIS_ALL_MAT_NOR_PU_FAR_QUA_PU_PEN_PRE_DEC_HA_QUA_CHE_LO_REN_VI_["eng"] = u"Well, a living being is something more than just matter. We can do some things... We can think, make decisions... we have something that makes us \"alive\"..."
LDP._0027_03_Bibliotecario_TIPO_UNANIMA_["eng"] = u"Like... a soul?"
LDP._0027_04_Tu_S_TIP_UNA_COS_DEL_GEN_["eng"] = u"Yeah, like... something like that..."
LDP._0027_05_Bibliotecario_CER_PU_AVE_SEN_MA_IL_RAG_NON_CAM__POS_CHE_ESI_UN_NON_MAT_ANC_SE_MOL_IMP_PER_IL_MOD_IN_CUI_QUE_SI_EVO_E_INT_CON_LA_REA__DET_DA_SPE_REG_["eng"] = u"Right, might make sense - however, the reasoning doesn't change. It is possible that nonmaterial \"soul\" exists - although very unlikely - but still... the way it evolves and interacts with reality is determined by specific rules..."
LDP._0027_06_Bibliotecario_NON_NON_SIA_POS_DIM_CI_CHE_LO_FA_SEM_OVV__CHE_GLI_UMA_SON_IN_GRA_DI_SPI_IL_MOT_DEL_LOR_AZI_E_SE_CI_SON_DEI_MOT_VUO_DIR_CHE_ANC_POT_TOR_IND_NEL_TEM_LE_AZI_COM_SAR_SEM_LE_STE_["eng"] = u"Even if it's impossible to prove, what makes it seem reasonable is that humans are able to explain the reasoning behind their actions. And, if there are reasons, it means that even if we could turn back time the events would still be the same."
LDP._0027_07_Tu_MMH_["eng"] = u"... <*>#italic#Mmh...<*>"
LDP._0027_08_Bibliotecario_FAC_FIN_CHE_SIA_POS_TOR_IND_NEL_TEM_TOR_A_UNA_SIT_IN_CUI_HAI_PRE_UNA_SCE_UNA_SCE_QUA_PER_FAC_PER_ANC_I_RIC_CHE_HAI_ACC_NEL_TEM_CHE_STA_RIA_DAC_["eng"] = u"Let's pretend we can travel back to the past. You want to go back to a certain time where you made a choice. Any choice. The thing is: in doing so you're losing all the memories you've stored up until the time you're going back to, right?"
LDP._0027_09_Tu_OK_MA_DEV_IMM_UNA_SIT_SPE_O_["eng"] = u"Oh, I see. Do I have to think about a specific situation or...?"
LDP._0027_10_Bibliotecario_NO_NON_IMP_VA_BEH_FAC_CHE_TOR_A_UNA_SIT_CHE_VOR_CAM_UN_EPI_DOV_HAI_COM_UNA_SCE_SB_ADE_HAI_LOC_DI_TOR_IND_E_SIS_LE_COS_PER_FAC_SCO_TUT_QUE_CHE__SUC_DOP_AVE_PRE_QUE_SCE_["eng"] = u"It doesn't really matter... well, let's get you back to some event you'd like to change. A specific time where you made a \"wrong\" choice. Now you have a chance to go back and fix it. But by doing so you'll forget everything that happened after you made that choice."
LDP._0027_11_Tu_VA_BEN_TOR_IND_ANC_CON_I_RIC_QUI_["eng"] = u"Alright, so I'll think back to a specific memory..."
LDP._0028_01_Tu_MMMH_["eng"] = u"<*>#italic#Mmmh...<*>"
LDP._0028_02_Bibliotecario__["eng"] = u"..."
LDP._0028_03_Tu__ALLORA_["eng"] = u"... <*>#italic#Mmmh...<*>"
LDP._0028_04_Bibliotecario__UNA_COS_QUA_["eng"] = u"... Anything..."
LDP._0028_05_Tu_S_STO_PEN_NON_POS_SPR_QUE_["eng"] = u"Yes yes, I'm thinking. I can't waste this opportunity."
LDP._0028_06_Bibliotecario__NON_SUC_VER_["eng"] = u"... It's not really going to happen..."
LDP._0028_07_Tu_ASP_CI_SON_QUA_["eng"] = u"Give me a second - almost there."
LDP._0028_08_Bibliotecario_MA_["eng"] = u"But..."
LDP._0028_09_Tu__VA_BEN_CI_SON_["eng"] = u"... All right, I got it!"
LDP._0028_10_Bibliotecario_OK_MI_RAC_HAI_PER_I_RIC_CHE_HAI_ACC_DA_QUE_MOM_FIN_AD_ADE_["eng"] = u"Ok. Keep in mind, you've lost all your memories from that moment until now."
LDP._0028_11_Tu_S_S_CI_SON_["eng"] = u"Sure, sure. I'm ready."
LDP._0028_12_Bibliotecario_PER_SEI_IN_QUE_SIT_NEL_MOM_IMM_PRI_A_QUE_IN_CUI_PRE_LA_TUA_DEC_OGN_COS__IDE_A_COM_TU_STA_PEN_ESA_A_QUE_CHE_PEN_IN_QUE_MOM_E_NON_SAI_COS_SUC_DIM__POS_CHE_TU_FAC_QUA_DI_DIV_CHE_TU_AGI_IN_MAN_INC_RIS_A_QUE_PRO_MEN_CHE_TI_HAN_POR_AD_AGI_COM_HAI_AGI_LA_PRI_VOL_["eng"] = u"Excellent. You're in that situation. The instant right before you make that decision. Everything is the same as it was, you're thinking exactly what you were thinking at the time and you don't know what's going to happen... Tell me, is it possible that you do something different? That you act inconsistently with those mental processes that led you to act as you did the first time?"
LDP._0028_13_Tu__AVR_POT_AVR_POT_["eng"] = u"... I could have... I could have..."
LDP._0028_14_Bibliotecario__["eng"] = u"..."
LDP._0028_15_Tu_BEH_SE_PEN_ALL_STE_COS_NON_SO_TUT_QUE_CHE_HO_FAT_E_PEN_SON_LA_CAU_DEL_MIA_DEC_QUI_["eng"] = u"Well, if I was thinking the same thing... I don't know, everything I've done and thought is what caused me to take that decision, so..."
LDP._0028_16_Bibliotecario_ESA_SON_LA_CAU_E_SAR_ASS_PEN_CHE_DAL_MED_CON_DI_PAR_POS_ESS_SCA_EFF_DIV_TRA_LOR_["eng"] = u"Exactly. It's the <*>#italic#cause.<*> And it would be absurd to think that the same starting conditions could lead to different endings!"
LDP._0028_17_Tu_SON_LA_CAU_["eng"] = u"It's the cause..."
LDP._0028_18_Bibliotecario_NON_HAI_MER_O_COL_DI_QUA_COS_TU_ABB_FAT_DET_O_PEN_NEL_TUA_VIT_SEM_SUC_DEG_EVE_CHE_TI_IMP_DEL_REA_PUN_PER_COS_CHE_HAI_FAT_O_CHE_TI_SON_SUC_SAR_COM_PUN_QUE_PAL_PER_QUA_PEN_CHE_SI_FER_TRO_PRE_O_TRO_TAR_PRI_DI_TOR_IND_SE_LE_CON_DI_PAR_SON_LE_STE_I_RIS_NON_CAM_["eng"] = u"There's no credit or blame for whatever you did, said or thought in your life. Events just happen to you. And those same events require a reaction. Punishing yourself for things you've done or happened to you would be like punishing this ball because someone thinks it stops too soon or too late before it comes back. If the starting conditions are the same, the results will not change."
LDP._0029_01_Tu_MA_ASP_COS_PER_NES_SAR_RES_DEL_PRO_AZI_SE_OGN_SCE_DIP_DA_QUE_CHE_CI_SUC_NON_SON_VER_SCE_PER_DOV_IMP_A_CIO_NON_CI_SAR_MOT_DI_CIO_["eng"] = u"Wait a second... no one would be responsible for their actions then... if every choice depends on what happens to us... they're not real choices. Why should I commit to... I mean, there would be no reason to... I mean..."
LDP._0029_02_Bibliotecario_S_INF_PER_QUE__COM_CHE_LE_PER_PEN_DI_AVE_LIB_ARB_LE_POR_A_IMP_PER_DEG_OBI_A_DAR_IMP_ALL_LOR_AZI_A_RES_A_SEG_LE_REG_LE_REN_PUN_QUA_SB_COS_SI_PEN_E_SI_EVO_SEC_LA_VIS_CHE_GLI_SI_VUO_IMP_LE_POR_A_OBB_SE_COS_NON_FOS_SAR_UN_PRO_ORG_DEL_SOC_["eng"] = u"Yes, indeed. That's why it's convenient for people to think they have free will. It pushes them to create objectives, to give importance to their actions, to be responsible, to follow the rules. It makes them punishable when they \"make mistakes\", so that they repent and evolve according to the vision imposed on them. It drives them to obey. If it wasn't that way organizing societies would be a huge problem."
LDP._0029_03_Tu__BEH_E_TU_PUR_SAP_QUE_COS_NON_SEI_UN_PRO_PER_LA_SOC_NO_["eng"] = u"... Well, what about you? Even if you know these things, you're not a problem for society, are you?"
LDP._0029_04_Bibliotecario_IO_ACC_LE_CON_FIN_MI_POR_VAN_PER_QUA_MI_RIG__MOL_MEG_CON_CON_LAV_STA_CHE_CON_ORG_IST_E_BES_LI_DAL_LOR_ARB_MI_MET_COM_CON_I_MIE_STU_E_OSS_["eng"] = u"I accept conventions as long as they bring me advantages. As far as I am concerned, it's much better to live with tired workers rather than with instinctive and savage beings, \"freed\" from their will. I sit back, relax, carry on my studies and observe."
LDP._0029_05_Tu_OK_MA_QUI_TU_TI_CON_UN_OR_IST_E_BES_LIB_DAL_TUO_ARB_["eng"] = u"Oh ok. So... do you consider yourself an \"instinctive and savage being freed from your will\" then?"
LDP._0029_06_Bibliotecario__BEH_QUA_CI_PEN_MA_FIN_NON_PEN_O_PEN_GLI_ALT_SON_UN_IND_RES_["eng"] = u"... Um, yes, when I think about it. But unless I'm not thinking or others do it instead of me I'm a responsible individual..."
LDP._0029_07_Tu__OK_MA_NON_MI_SEM_MOL_IS_O_BE_ORA_CHE_CI_STA_PEN_["eng"] = u"... Right... you don't seem very \"instinctive\" or \"savage\" now you're thinking about it..."
LDP._0029_08_Bibliotecario_SAR_LO_SON_IO_E_LO_SEI_TU_TAN_QUA_LO_SON_LE_API_LE_FOR_E_I_CAS_QUA_COS_ALV_FOR_E_DIG_IO_POS_COS_EDI_DIS_IMM_E_SCR_LIB_QUE_DOV_REN_NO_IST_SIA_UNA_SPE_ANI_TRA_TAN_ALT_LA_DIF_TRA_NAT_E_ART_SER_SOL_A_NOI_PER_INN_IL_NOS_LAV_PER_REN_PI_NOB_PI_IMP_["eng"] = u"Sara... I am, and you are, and so are bees, ants and beavers building hives, anthills and dams. I can raise walls, draw pictures and write books... should this make me \"not instinctive\"? We're an animal species among many others. We created the difference between 'natural' and 'artificial' only to elevate our purpose, to make it nobler, more relevant..."
LDP._0029_09_Tu_MH_["eng"] = u"Hmm..."
LDP._0029_10_Bibliotecario_COM_A_PRO_DI_LAV_DOV_TOR_AL_MIO_ADE_DIC_DI_ESS_VEN_PER_SAP_DI_TUO_FRA_["eng"] = u"Anyway, speaking of work, I should get back to mine now. You said you came by to search for your brother..."
LDP._0029_11_Tu__S_S_MIO_FRA_VOL_SAP_SE_FOS_PAS_DI_QUI__SCA_DI_CAS_IER_NOT_DA_UN_PO_DI_TEM_DIC_DI_VOL_VEN_IN_CIT_QUI_LHO_SEG_HO_CHI_IN_GIR_E_MI__STA_DET_DI_CON_IN_BIB_["eng"] = u"... Yes, exactly, my brother! I wanted to know if he's been here. He ran away from home last night. He would always fantasize about coming to the city, that's why I came here. I've been asking around and I was suggested to try the library..."
LDP._0029_12_Bibliotecario_SE_TUO_FRA__PAS_DI_QUI_LO_VED_SUB_DAI_REG_["eng"] = u"If your brother's been here it's definitely recorded in the logs..."
LDP._0030_01_Bibliotecario_IL_NOME_["eng"] = u"Name?"
LDP._0030_02_Tu_HANS_["eng"] = u"Hans."
LDP._0030_03_Bibliotecario_HAN_NO_NON_C_NES_HAN_QUI_POT_ESS_PRE_CON_UN_NOM_DIV_["eng"] = u"Hans... no... there's no Hans here. Could he've used a different name?"
LDP._0030_04_Tu_NON_CRE_PER_AVR_DOV_["eng"] = u"I don't think so... why would he?"
LDP._0030_05_Bibliotecario_SE_N_AND_SEN_DIR_NIE_NON_CRE_CHE_VOL_ESS_SEG_NON_MI_OST_TRO_FOS_IN_TE_MAG_UN_GIO_VI_RIN_["eng"] = u"If he left without saying anything, I don't think he wanted to be chased... I wouldn't get hung up on it if I were you. Maybe one day you'll meet again."
LDP._0030_06_Tu_S_SAI_A_CHI_ALT_POT_CHI_["eng"] = u"Yeah sure... do you know someone else i could ask?"
LDP._0030_07_Bibliotecario_COM_VUO_IN_EFF_QUA_C_E_MI_FAR_ANC_UN_BEL_FAV_SE_CI_AND_["eng"] = u"Never mind... There is someone actually. You would also do me a great favor if you went there..."
LDP._0030_08_Bibliotecario_DEV_FAR_UNA_CON_A_UN_MIO_VEC_AMI_VIV_A_SUD_OLT_LA_SEL_ARI_SI_CHI_NEI__UNA_PER_MOL_POT_CHE_HA_NOT_DI_TUT_GLI_SPO_CHE_AVV_IN_QUE_TER_DA_QUE_CHE_HO_CAP__POS_CHE_TUO_FRA_NON_SIA_IN_CIT_QUI_SE_C_UNA_PER_A_CUI_DOV_CHI__SEN_DUB_NEI_["eng"] = u"I have to deliver something to an old friend of mine. He lives south beyond the Barren Forest. His name's Neil, he's a very powerful guy who knows and monitors all the movements in the land. From what I understand, it's possible your brother isn't even in town... so if there's one person you should be asking, it's definitely Neil."
LDP._0030_09_Tu_MMH_NON_PEN_SE_NE_SIA_AND_DAL_CIT_RIS_DI_PER_SOL_TEM_["eng"] = u"<*>#italic#Umm...<*> I don't think he went far from the city... I can't risk wasting time..."
LDP._0030_10_Bibliotecario_NON_SAI_NEM_SE_CI__MAI_STA_IN_CIT_MAG__ADE_CHE_STA_PER_TEM_["eng"] = u"You don't even know if he's ever been in town, maybe you're wasting your time just now."
LDP._0030_11_Tu_UFF_E_QUE_NEI_VOR_AIU_["eng"] = u"<*>#italic#Hmm...<*> will this Neil be willing to help me?"
LDP._0030_12_Bibliotecario_CER_SAR_MOL_FEL_DI_RIC_CI_CHE_GLI_CON_["eng"] = u"No doubt. He'll be very happy to receive what I'm giving you."
LDP._0030_13_Tu__E_COS_DOV_CON_["eng"] = u"... What am I supposed to deliver?"
LDP._0030_14_Bibliotecario_TI_FAC_VED_["eng"] = u"I'll show you..."
LDP._0031_01_Bibliotecario__LAV_MES_QUA_DA_QUA_PAR_["eng"] = u"... I put it in here somewhere..."
LDP._0032_01_Bibliotecario__ERA_QUI_["eng"] = u"... It was here..."
LDP._0032_02_Bibliotecario__AH_TRO_["eng"] = u"... Ah! Found it."
LDP._0033_01_Bibliotecario_ECCO_QUI_["eng"] = u"There you go."
LDP._0033_02_Tu__COS_["eng"] = u"... What's this thing?"
LDP._0033_03_Bibliotecario_QUE__UNA_CRE_DEL_MON_OCC_APP_A_UNA_SPE_CHE_SI__EST_DA_DIV_ANN_ORM_MA_SON_RIU_A_CON_UN_ESE_["eng"] = u"An ancient creature of the western mountains. It's a species that has been extinct for several years now, but I managed to preserve a specimen."
LDP._0033_04_Tu_MA__VIV_["eng"] = u"Is it... alive?"
LDP._0033_05_Bibliotecario_S_CER_QUE_BES_SON_PRA_IMM_SON_IN_GRA_DI_CO_PER_MOL_ANN_FIN_NON_TRO_NUT_["eng"] = u"Yes, of course. These beasts are pretty much immortal. They can \"freeze\" for decades until they find nourishment."
LDP._0033_06_Tu_AH_E_COM_HAN_FAT_A_EST_ALL_["eng"] = u"Oh, how did they go extinct then?"
LDP._0033_07_Bibliotecario_QUE__UNA_BEL_DOM_SON_SPA_TUT_IN_UNA_NOT_DI_CIR_DIE_ANN_FA_DI_COL_NON_SE_NE_SON_PI_VIS_IN_GIR_UN_EPI_PIU_STR_CHE__STA_IGN_DA_MOL_PER_VIA_DEI_DIS_AVV_NEL_SEL_E_NEL_LAG_QUA_GIO_DOP_["eng"] = u"That's a good question. About ten years ago, on a night like any others, they all disappeared. Just like that... they were nowhere to be found. A pretty strange occurrence that quickly faded into the background due the disasters that affected the forest and the lake just a few days later..."
LDP._0033_08_Bibliotecario_PER_QUE_SOL_POC_STU_SI_INT_ALL_QUE_MA_IO_ERO_TRA_QUE_SON_PAR_ALL_RIC_DI_UNA_QUA_SPI_VER_OVE_E_SON_RIU_A_TRO_QUE_PIC_IMP_INC_IN_UNA_ROC_COS_LHO_PRE_E_HO_INI_A_STU_["eng"] = u"That's why very few researchers were interested in the matter. But I was one of them. I left and went searching for signs to the west and managed to find this little impo stuck in a rock. So I took it and started studying it."
LDP._0033_09_Tu_IMP_SI_CHI_COS_["eng"] = u"Impo? Is that a name?"
LDP._0033_10_Bibliotecario_IM__IL_NOM_DEL_SPE_GLI__STA_DAT_PER_POR_UNI_SUL_NUC_CHE_FOR_QUE_SCR_["eng"] = u"\"Impo\" is the name of the species. It was given to them because they all have it carved on their nape..."
LDP._0033_11_Tu_UNI_CHE_DIC_IM_["eng"] = u"An engraving that says \"Impo\"...?"
LDP._0033_12_Bibliotecario_COM_IO_LHO_OSS_ABB_E_NON_SAP_COS_RIC_NEI_STA_INI_A_INT_MA_DA_QUE_CHE_SO_NON_NE_HA_MAI_POT_OSS_UNO_DA_VIC_SE_GLI_LAS_STU_POT_DED_QUA_IN_PI_["eng"] = u"I've observed it enough by the way and I don't know what else to get from it. Neil started becoming interested in impos but as far as I know, he never got a chance to see one up close. If I let him have this, he could find out something more."
LDP._0033_13_Tu__VA_BEN_COM_LO_TRA_["eng"] = u"... Alright. How do I carry it?"
LDP._0033_14_Bibliotecario_NON_DEV_TRA_TI_SEG_QUA_ATT_QUE_PIE_["eng"] = u"Carry it? No... once you activate this stone it'll follow you."
LDP._0034_01_Tu_SI__SVE_["eng"] = u"Did he wake up?!"
LDP._0034_02_Bibliotecario_LHO_APP_ALI_NON_TI_PRE_NON__AGG_["eng"] = u"I just fed it. Don't worry, he's not aggressive."
LDP._0034_03_Tu_OK_QUI_ADE_MI_SEG_["eng"] = u"Ok... So now he'll follow me?"
LDP._0034_04_Bibliotecario_SEG_SEM_LA_PIE_CHE_TI_HO_DAT_QUA__ATT_MA_CI_CHE_REN_VER_INT_QUE_CRE__IL_SUO_COM_QUA_LA_PIE__SPE_["eng"] = u"It follows the stone I gave you when it's activated. But what really makes this creature interesting is what it does when the stone is turned off."
LDP._0034_05_Tu_ADE__SPE_E_NON_STA_FAC_NIE_["eng"] = u"It's off now and... it's not doing anything."
LDP._0034_06_Bibliotecario_GLI_IMP_SON_MOL_RAZ_E_MET_ESE_SEM_LAZ_CHE_RIT_PRI_PER_LE_CIR_LO_FAN_FIN_NON_ESA_LE_ENE_A_QUE_PUN_SI_FER_E_ASP_IL_NUT_ADE_SEM_STR_MA_LA_PRI_DI_QUE_IMP__RIM_FER_E_CI_RES_FIN_QUA_NON_GLI_DIR_DI_FAR_QUA_["eng"] = u"Impos are extremely rational and methodical. They always act as to what they consider a priority according to the circumstances. They do it until they run out of energy, then they stop and wait for nourishment. Now, it may seem strange, but the priority right now is to stand still. And he'll stay like that until someone tells him to do something else."
LDP._0034_07_Tu_QUA_POS_POS_DIR_COS_FAR_["eng"] = u"Someone...? We can... I can tell him what to do?"
LDP._0034_08_Bibliotecario_PUO_DIR_CHE_AZI_COM_A_SEC_DEL_SIT_E_LUI_LA_ESE_OGN_VOL_SEN_BAT_CIG_MA_PER_COM_QUE_INF_DEV_INS_DEG_IMP_NEL_CHE_HA_DIE_LA_TES_QUE_APE_VEN_CHI_CE_DI_MEM_E_LUI_NE_HA_SOL_UNA_AL_MOM_QUI_PUO_FAR_FAR_SOL_UNA_ALL_VOL_["eng"] = u"You can tell him what to do depending on the situation and he'll perform the action without even thinking about it. But to pass him the information you have to insert some impoleaves into the opening behind his head. These slits are called \"memory slots\" and he has only one at the moment, so you can have it perform only one action at a time."
LDP._0034_09_Tu_AH_E_COS_UN_IM_["eng"] = u"Ok... and what is an \"impoleaf\"?"
LDP._0034_10_Bibliotecario_LIM__UNA_SPE_DI_FOG_NON_MOL_SPE_MA_FAT_DI_UN_MAT_MOL_PI_RIG_E_RES_DEL_CAR_NOR_TUT_GLI_IMP_SON_DIV_TRA_LOR_E_SI_DIV_IN_DUE_CAT_CO_CHE_IND_DEL_CON_E_AZ_CHE_IND_DEL_AZI_DA_COM_["eng"] = u"An impoleaf is some sort of sheet, not very thick but made of a very rigid and resistant material - it's different than normal paper. Each impoleaf is different from the others. They're divided into two categories: \"Conditio-Impoleaves\", which indicate the conditions, and \"Actio-Impoleaves\", which indicate the actions to be performed..."
LDP._0034_11_Bibliotecario_PER_DAR_UNI_A_UN_IMP_DEV_INS_UN_CON_E_UN_AZI_NEL_CEL_DI_MEM_LIM_OGN_VOL_CHE_DEV_DEC_COS_FAR_LEG_LA_CON_E_LAZ_NEL_CEL_E_SE_VAL_DI_TRO_NEL_SIT_ADA_ESE_LIS_ALT_STA_FER_["eng"] = u"To give impos an instruction you must enter a Conditio-Impoleaf and an Actio-Impoleaf in the memory cell. Every time the impo has to decide what to do, it reads the condition and the action: if it thinks they align with the situation, it follows the instructions. Otherwise it won't move."
LDP._0034_12_Tu_OK_SEM_ABB_COM_["eng"] = u"Okay, that sounds pretty complicated."
LDP._0034_13_Bibliotecario_CER_SE_VUO_DAR_UNO_IN_BIB_CI_SON_DIV_LIB_CHE_PAR_PI_DET_DEL_LOR_FUN_MA_SON_SIC_CHE_IMP_IN_FRE_FAC_QUA_PRO_AL_MOM_IO_HO_SOL_QUE_DUE_DI_IMP_QUE_CON_IND_UNA_SIT_IN_CUI_QUA_VUO_AGG_MEN_QUE_AZI_FA_ESE_UN_ATT_FOL_["eng"] = u"Very much... If you want to take a look, there are several books in the library that go into detail about how they work. But I'm sure you'll learn best by doing a few tests. At the moment I only have these two impoleaves: this Conditio-Impoleaf identifies a situation in which someone wants to attack you and this Actio-Impoleaf performs a withering attack."
LDP._0034_14_Tu_WOW_POS_FAR_FAR_ORA_["eng"] = u"Oh wow... Can we get him to do it now?"
