LDP._0120_01_Tu_QUE_LIB_SIN_SU_COS_VOL__TEM__QUE_["eng"] = u"(This book reads: \"On Consciousness Vol.3 - Time\"... that's the one!)"
LDP._0120_02_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol3Tempo__SVI_LIP_PER_CUI_LA_REA_SI_EVO_IN_MOD_DET_VIE_SPO_CHI_IN_CHE_MOD_IL_TEM_SCO_IN_AVA_POT_CON_DUE_POS_IL_TEM__COM_DA_UN_SUS_DI_EVE_DET_E_SEP_TRA_LOR_OPP_DA_UN_FL_INF_DI_EVE_IND_E_INS_TRA_LOR_["eng"] = u"... Developing the hypothesis for which reality it's determined, one might wonder how comes time goes forward. We could consider two scenarios. One: time is a succession of events which are determined and independent. Two: time is like an infinite \"flow\" of events which are indistinguishable and inseparable from one other."
LDP._0120_03_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol3Tempo__PRE_LA_PRI_IPO_IN_CUI_GLI_EVE_SON_DIS_E_SEP_DOV_IPO_CHE_TRA_UN_EVE_E_LAL_CI_SIA_UN_MO_IN_CUI_IL_TEM_NON_SCO_MA_IN_CUI_AVV_UN_QUA_COS_CHE_PER_ALL_SUC_DI_AVV_DOV_IPO_CHE_CI_SIA_UNA_SOR_DI_MO_IMM_CHE_SEN_ESS_MOS_O_CA_DA_ALT_EVE_RIE_A_FAR_SCO_SPO_LA_SEQ_TEM_IN_AVA_["eng"] = u"... Taking the first hypothesis - in which events are independent and can be distinguished - we then should assume that, between one event and another, there is a \"moment\" in which time does not pass, but in which something happens that allows the next event to occur. We should assume that there is some sort of \"unmoved mover\" that, without being moved or \"caused\" by other events, it spontaneously manages to slide the timeline forward."
LDP._0120_04_Tu_ECC_TRA_UN_EVE_E_LAL_HAN_ES_PI_DI_QUE_DUE_MIN_PER_CON_QUE_APP_CON_A_VIV_MEN_IL_TEM_ERA_BLO_840_ANN_PER_OGN_EVE_CHE_PAS_PER_UN_TOT_DI_700_MIL_DI_ANN_IN_DUE_MIN_["eng"] = u"(Here! Between two events... they \"experienced\" more than those two minutes because of that device - they kept living as time stopped... 100 million years for every event that passed... for a total of 700 billion years... in two minutes...)"
